descript.abstract: This roadway spatial database was created in conjunction with the Wisconsin Winter Maintenance Concept Vehicle at UW-Madison by the UW-Madison WiscPlow Research Team. It depicts the roadway centerlines in Portage County and contains attributes used by the WiscPlow software, among them attributes necessary to create a network shapefile using Netshape. The spatial features were first obtained from the Portage County Land Information Office, and only slightly adjusted when necessary to provide the topological integrity required by WiscPlow. Orthophotos obtained from the Portage County Land Information Office were used as a reference for spatial changes made to the original dataset.
descript.purpose: This roadway centerline database was created by the UW-Madison WiscPlow Research Team solely for use with the WiscPlow software, also developed by the UW-Madison Research Team. The attributes contained in the shapefile were created to fulfill the specific requirements of the WiscPlow program, and may not have any other intuitive meaning. This dataset is not intended to be used for any other reason than with the WiscPlow application.

timeperd.current: This data set was originally produced in 2005, using the most current information available from the Portage County Land Information Office. The Portage County Highway Department will update this data as they deem necessary for their operations.

idinfo.accconst: This dataset is intended to be used only by the Portage County Highway Department for use with WiscPlow. It will be their duty to maintain and update this dataset in the future. This dataset is not intended to be reproduced or redistributed to any other parties.

procstep.procdesc: All necessary attributes for the creation of topology were added to the dataset. Dataset copied.
A clean function was used within ArcGIS 9.0 to snap unsnapped nodes that were disrupting the creation of a network topology for the dataset. Dataset copied.
A couple small roadways needed for topology were manually digitized. Dataset copied.
More manual digitizing was done, mostly to separate interstate ramps into their principal components. Dataset copied.
Fields were deleted, remaining fields were renamed, and unnamed roads were given names. Some polylines were merged. Dataset copied.
Patrol sections were attributed for the entire county. Dataset copied.
Attributes were recalculated and verified for correctness. Dataset copied.
Dataset cleaned up, attributes recalculated. Dataset copied.
Patrol sections were edited. Some roads were renamed, polylines were merged and split. Dataset copied.
Patrol sections were edited. Lengths and topology fields were recalculated. Dataset copied.

attracc.attraccr: The accuracy of the attributes is subject to human error and limited by the accuracy of the dataset from which it was derived. Attributes were changed and added to the original dataset obtained from the Portage County Land Information Office as needed. Every effort was made to insure the correctness of the attributes, in order that the WiscPlow software function properly.

dataqual.logic: This dataset is topologically structured for arcs for the entire Portage County area. The geographic data represented by this shapefile is represented according to a vector-based data type.
dataqual.complete: The features represented in this dataset are, to the best knowledge of the UW-Madison WiscPlow Research Team, representative of all roadway centerlines in Portage County of importance to the functionality of the WiscPlow software. The features will need to be updated in the future.

horizpa.horizpar: Accuracy of this data is entirely dependent upon the accuracy of the source roadway centerline dataset obtained from the Portage County Land Information Office which was used to create this data. The original source dataset was heads-up digitized from USGS digital orthophoto quarterquads (nominal scale = 1:12,000) in 1997. Some spatial features were adjusted to countywide orthophotos acquired in 2000. Other spatial features were changed by the Portage County Land Information Office to reflect newly constructed roadways since 2000. Minor changes were made to horizontal coordinates of spatial features by the UW-Madison WiscPlow Research Team only when deemed necessary for the topology required by WiscPlow.

vertacc.vertaccr: There is no vertical data in this dataset.
